				\begin{document}$$i \in [1,m]$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M518"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">[</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">]</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq260.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. The <italic>i</italic>th iteration of the last loop in the algorithm computes the maximum in a range <inline-formula id="IEq261"><alternatives><tex-math id="M519">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$d'_{k-1}[i',i]$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M520"><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>d</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">[</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">]</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq261.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, where <inline-formula id="IEq262"><alternatives><tex-math id="M521">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$d'_{k-1}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M522"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>d</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq262.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is the original array <inline-formula id="IEq263"><alternatives><tex-math id="M523">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$d_{k-1}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M524"><mml:msub><mml:mi>d</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq263.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> before modifications and <inline-formula id="IEq264"><alternatives><tex-math id="M525">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$i' = P[b] + 1$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M526"><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">[</mml:mo><mml:mi>b</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">]</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq264.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> for some <italic>b</italic> and <italic>P</italic>. Let <inline-formula id="IEq265"><alternatives><tex-math id="M527">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\ell _i = i - i'$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M528"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq265.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. Denote <inline-formula id="IEq266"><alternatives><tex-math id="M529">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\tilde{\ell }} = \frac{1}{m} \sum _{i=1}^m \ell _i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M530"><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:mfrac><mml:msubsup><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msub><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq266.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, the “average query length”. We are to prove that the running time of the algorithm is <inline-formula id="IEq267"><alternatives><tex-math id="M531">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$O(m\log {\tilde{\ell }})$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M532"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>O</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mo>log</mml:mo><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq267.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, which implies the result since <inline-formula id="IEq268"><alternatives><tex-math id="M533">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$m{\tilde{\ell }} = \sum _{i=1}^m \ell _i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M534"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msub><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq268.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq269"><alternatives><tex-math id="M535">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sum _{i=1}^m \ell _i \le |\Sigma | m$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M536"><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mo>∑</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:msub><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>≤</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">|</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">Σ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">|</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq269.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. The latter inequality follows from the fact that the query ranges correponding to the same symbol are non-overlapping.</p>
          <p>We say that a position <italic>j</italic> is <italic>touched</italic> if the function <inline-formula id="IEq270"><alternatives><tex-math id="M537">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathsf {maxd}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M538"><mml:mi mathvariant="sans-serif">maxd</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq270.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is called with its first argument equal to <italic>j</italic>. Since for each <italic>i</italic> the first call to <inline-formula id="IEq271"><alternatives><tex-math id="M539">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathsf {maxd}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M540"><mml:mi mathvariant="sans-serif">maxd</mml:mi></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq271.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is with different <italic>j</italic>, it suffices to prove that the total number of touches is <inline-formula id="IEq272"><alternatives><tex-math id="M541">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$O(m\log {\tilde{\ell }})$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M542"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>O</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mo>log</mml:mo><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>ℓ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">~</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq272.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. While processing the query <inline-formula id="IEq273"><alternatives><tex-math id="M543">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
