				\begin{document}$$P = O(m\log m)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M608"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mi>O</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mo>log</mml:mo><mml:mi>m</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq304.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. But we can deduce a stronger bound. Since the sum of all values <inline-formula id="IEq305"><alternatives><tex-math id="M609">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
