				\begin{document}$${\mathcal {R}} = \{R_1, \ldots , R_m\}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M900"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">R</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo stretchy="false">{</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mo>…</mml:mo><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mi>m</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo stretchy="false">}</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2019_147_Article_IEq448.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, <italic>each of which has length</italic> <italic>n</italic>. <italic>For</italic><inline-formula id="IEq449"><alternatives><tex-math id="M901">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
